Thats a cool vid, I came across that not to long ago aswell...   Hopefully his parents take good care of his fingers. Lots of talented kids lose their ability early in life due to arthritis (sp?)

He'll probably be doing a lot of this...   Jimmy Bowskill at 15 yrs old. My buddy Wayne Deadder on bass, Tortoise Blue on the boards both from Big Daddy G and Al Cross on drums formally of Jane Sibery's band.  When you see Jimmy play you quickly forget about his age and you become awestruck with the connection he has with that guitar. -Brian
Both guitarists are very talented!!  I could sit and listen to them all day....wait...I'm at work...maybe I will....
The kid is definately gifted at playin, impressive!
I've heard of him, but never heard him. Not too shabby.  JF
And to think,he,s doing it drug free.LOL jambolya  Can someone tell me how to make the screen come up instead of the link? Thanks mucho.
That's impressive  Always amazes me that some people just seem to be born with a natural talent for some things---just need the right environment to bring it out.
